history.content:
Currently, no it cannot count to fulfill that requirement. If you go to this website and look at the course descriptions for courses that fulfill the EECS design requirement, you will see that each curriculum is centered around learning the design process of whatever the topic is.

If you feel that it should count, I recommend you talk to the professor to make sure she feels the same. And then email Emerald about taking steps to get that changed!
Can 161 be considered as a design course to fullfill the EECS design requirement? I saw it on the website that it cannot, but there are many design projects in 161...
